SIMPLE: leatherleaf
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: leatherleaf
<hw>leatherleaf</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stiff
leathery-leaved fern (<spn>Polypodium scouleri</spn>) of Western North
America having ovate fronds parted to the midrib.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leathery polypody, coast polypody, <spn>Polypodium
scouleri</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A northern temperate bog shrub (<spn>Chamaedaphne
calyculata</spn>) with evergreen leathery leaves and small white
cylindrical flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Chamaedaphne calyculata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>leatherlike</ent>⟦br⟧
